{"ts": "2026-06-09T16:44:23.851629+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Answer\n\n### Package Manager\n\nThe repository expects contributors to use **Yarn** as the package manager. Evidence:\n\n- `yarn.lock` is present in the root (no `package-lock.json`)\n- The `Taskfile.yaml` `init` task runs `yarn install`\n- The `package.json` `\"fix\"` script explicitly calls `yarn lint --fix`\n\n> **Note:** The `CONTRIBUTING.md` mentions a migration to npm is underway (\"*we standardize on npm for contributor setup now, so ignore any yarn-oriented scripts or labels that still appear in package metadata during migration*\"), but the project tooling still targets yarn.\n\n---\n\n### Environment-Specific Script Names\n\n#### Yarn / npm scripts (defined in `package.json`)\n\n| Script | Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `dev` | `cross-env NODE_ENV=local vite --host` | Local development server |\n| `dev:stg` | `cross-env NODE_ENV=stg vite` | Staging development server |\n| `build` | `vite build --mode prod` | Build (default/prod mode) |\n| `build:stg` | `cross-env vite build --mode test` | Staging build |\n| `build:prod` | `cross-env vite build --mode production` | Production build |\n| `serve` | `vite preview --host` | Preview the built dist |\n| `deploy` | `gh-pages -d dist` | Deploy to GitHub Pages |\n| `lint` | `eslint --ext .jsx,.js,.ts,.tsx .` | Lint the project |\n| `fix` | `yarn lint --fix` | Lint with auto-fix |\n\n#### Task runner scripts (defined in `Taskfile.yaml`, invoked via `task`)\n\n| Task | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `init` | Installs global tools (conventional-changelog-cli, standard-version, commitizen), copies `.env.local` → `.env`, runs `yarn install` |\n| `changelog` | Generates a changelog using `conventional-changelog` |\n| `release` | Fetches, runs `yarn release`, generates changelog, stages & commits |\n| `commit` | Stages all, commits via Commitizen, pushes |\n\n#### Environment files (`envs/` directory)\n\n| File | Environment |\n|---|---|\n| `.env.local` | Local development |\n| `.env.stg` | Staging |\n| `.env.prod` | Production |\n\nThe `vite.config.ts` loads the appropriate `.env` file based on the `NODE_ENV` value (falling back to `envs/.env.${NODE_ENV}`).", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1056, "prompt_tokens": 14335, "total_tokens": 15391, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 485, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 13760}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "08758acae36443668be9f628b40121d9", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead44-e56a-7053-92c2-6cfc248db86e-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 14335, "output_tokens": 1056, "total_tokens": 15391, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 13760}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 485}}}}]}}}
